{{Jainism}}
'''Harisena''' was a tenth century ''[[Digambara monk]]''. His origin is traced to those monks who had stayed in the north during the supposed famine and had been prevailed upon by their lay followers to cover their private parts with a strip of cloth (''ardhaphalaka'') while begging for alms.{{sfn|Dundas|2002|p=48}}

He wrote ''Brhatkathakosha'' in 932 AD.{{sfn|Jaini|1991|p=43}} The text talks about the stupas in Mathura being erected by devas during controversies with Buddhists.{{sfn|Umakant Premanand Shah|1987|p=16}}

