'''Hindu Religious Welfare Trust''' is a national government trust that looks after the welfare of the Hindu community of Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="fgh">{{cite web|last1=Rajbanshi|first1=Manoranjan|title=Hindu Welfare Trust|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Hindu_Welfare_Trust|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Govt firm to establish secular society: PM|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-152183|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=15 October 2016|date=25 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Ghosh|first1=Partha S.|title=The Politics of Personal Law in South Asia: Identity, Nationalism and the Uniform Civil Code|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781136705120|pages=181|url=https://books.google.com/?id=lwPgCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA181&lpg=PA181&dq=%22Hindu+Religious+Welfare+Trust%22#v=onepage&q=%22Hindu%20Religious%20Welfare%20Trust%22&f=false|accessdate=15 October 2016|language=en|date=2012-05-23}}</ref>
==History== The Hindu Religious Welfare Trust was established in 1983. It is under the [[Ministry of Religious Affairs (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Religious Affairs]].<ref name="fgh"></ref> In 2016-2017 budget session 2 billion taka was allocated to the trust by the finance ministry.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tk 200 crore for upkeep of Hindu temples|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/business/tk-200-crore-upkeep-hindu-temples-1233766|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=15 October 2016|date=3 June 2016}}</ref>
