'''John Stronach''' (1810-1888), younger brother of [[Alexander Stronach]], was a [[Protestant]] [[Christian]] missionary who served with the [[London Missionary Society]] during the late [[Qing Dynasty]] [[China]], working primarily at Xiamen [Amoy]. Stronach participated in the translation of bible into Chinese.

