A '''temple boy''' ({{lang-th|เด็กวัด}} ''dek wat'') is a boy in [[Thailand]] who lives in a [[wat]] and assists [[bhikkhu|Buddhist monks]]. 

The temple boys carry the [[alms]] bowls of the monks during the morning alms collection, and subsequently prepare the monks’ food before eating the leftovers themselves. They follow the [[Five Precepts#Ten Precepts|ten precepts]]. Some are sent to become temple boys to acquire [[Merit (Buddhism)|merit]]; others, because they are given free room and board; and others to receive [[religion|religious]] and [[morality|moral]] instruction. Some temple boys go on to be ordained as monks themselves.  Temple boys may undertake the formal step of [[śrāmaṇera|sāmaṇera]] ordination as part of their role, depending on their age and local custom.

