'''Waheguru''' ({{lang-pa|ਵਾਹਿਗੁਰੂ|translit=vāhigurū|translit-std=IAST}})  refers to  [[God in Sikhism|God]] in [[Sikhism]].

The word ''vāhegurū'' is [[folk etymology|traditionally explained]] as being composed of ''vāhe'' "wondrous", ''gu'' "darkness", and ''ru'' "light", together said to carry the meaning - The wondrous Lord who dispells the darkness of ignorance and bestows the light of truth, knowledge and enlightenment.{{cn|date=November 2018}}

The word ''Vaheguru or Waheguru'' is also used in Sikhism as a main [[mantra]], called {{lang|hi|gurmantra}} or {{lang|pa|gur mantar}}. 

